      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson residual norms < 1e-4 at every converged increment; energy criterion < 1e-3.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analysis employed full Newton-Raphson iteration. Force residual norm < 5e-5 and displacement residual norm < 8e-5 at all converged load increments. Energy criterion 3e-4. No unconverged increments in production runs. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of boundary conditions, loading definitions, and material assignments completed by analyst not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "Independent senior analyst reviewed boundary condition application (fixed inferior vertebral body, displacement-controlled superior loading block), contact definitions (frictional coefficient 0.2 at screw-rod interface), and Ti-6Al-4V material assignment. No errors identified. Review documented in project record PR-COU1-2024-07. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening validated for Ti-6Al-4V implant-grade material; contact mechanics representation consistent with physical construct assembly.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, Et=2 GPa) calibrated against coupon tensile data from same material lot. Surface-to-surface contact with augmented Lagrangian formulation captures screw-rod locking interface. Model form consistent with prior FDA validation studies of metallic spinal implants. Gradation 3 required and achieved given Medium model risk and COU sensitivity to material nonlinearity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws; torque preload documented.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus, yield strength, and ultimate strength measured from five tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock as test constructs. Screw geometry verified by CMM (±5 µm). Set-screw torque preload 4.0 N·m applied in FEA via pretension element, matching bench protocol. Coefficient of variation on material inputs < 3%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
