      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 test constructs from production lot; traceability of specimens to material certificates documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-lot screws and rods with full material traceability. Specimens distributed across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH Biomechanics Lab and DePuy Synthes R&D). Coefficient of variation on experimental stiffness 4.8%, indicating good specimen consistency. Exceeds Gradation 2 minimum; Gradation 3 awarded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct loading rates or environmental conditions to bracket COU; environmental conditioning documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) at ambient temperature per ASTM F1717. A second loading condition (e.g., 1 mm/min or physiological saline bath) was not included in this validation campaign. This factor falls one gradation below the required level. Risk accepted on the basis that rate sensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V at quasi-static rates is negligible per published literature; compensating margin provided by conservative acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions, preload) demonstrably equivalent to as-tested specimen conditions; deviations quantified.",
      "rationale": "Nominal FEA geometry updated to as-measured CMM dimensions for each of the 11 specimens. Material properties assigned from lot-specific coupon data. Boundary conditions replicate test fixture as documented in lab setup photographs and fixture drawings. Maximum geometric deviation between CAD and CMM < 0.05 mm. Equivalency formally documented in test-analysis correlation report TAC-COU1-2024. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using both percent difference (< 10%) and normalised error metric E/uval (< 1.96) for all three QoIs; uncertainty in experimental mean propagated.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: stiffness (E/uval=0.84, 4.2%), yield force (E/uval=1.12, 6.7%), force at 40 mm (E/uval=0.61, 3.1%). Experimental uncertainty estimated via GUM methodology including load cell calibration (±0.5%), displacement transducer (±0.1 mm), and inter-laboratory variability. All three QoIs pass both acceptance criteria. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are mechanistically linked to clinical failure modes (fatigue initiation, permanent deformation) and are the quantities used in the COU regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spinal segment; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are direct ASTM F1717 pass/fail metrics used in 510(k) submissions. All three QoIs are the same quantities predicted by the FEA in the COU. Relevance is direct and unambiguous. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
